<p>Here's the fiddle of my project <a href="https://jsfiddle.net/Optiq/65rddhu4/" rel="nofollow">https://jsfiddle.net/Optiq/65rddhu4/</a></p>  <p>If you look at the label on the right side that says "Strongest" you'll notice that it sits beneath even the div it's contained within.  I initially had the div narrower in width but even as I extend it out it still stays on the bottom.</p>  <p>I know a way to work around it is to use CSS to add a position attribute to force it to where I want it to be, but from my experience with positioning things like that it may look right in one browser but may be 400px away in a different browser.  Why is this occurring?</p>  <p>Here's the HMTL</p>  <pre><code>                &lt;div class="texfrm_o" style="height:128px;"&gt;                 &lt;div class="texfrm_i" style="width:99%; height:128px; margin:auto;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;                     &lt;label class="label_02" style="width:77%; text-align:center; margin:auto;"&gt;Generating Ideas&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br /&gt;                     &lt;div class="anscont"&gt;                         &lt;div class="r_cont_lab" style="float:left; margin-left:4px;"&gt;                             Weakest                         &lt;/div&gt;                          &lt;div class="radcont"&gt;                             &lt;div class="radbox"&gt;                                 &lt;label for="q7a1" class="rad_lab"&gt;1&lt;/label&gt;                                 &lt;input type="radio" class="rad_buttn2" value="1" name="Generating Ideas" id="q7a1"&gt;                             &lt;/div&gt;                              &lt;div class="radbox"&gt;                                 &lt;label for="q7a2" class="rad_lab"&gt;2&lt;/label&gt;                                 &lt;input type="radio" class="rad_buttn2" value="2" name="Generating Ideas" id="q7a2"&gt;                             &lt;/div&gt;                              &lt;div class="radbox"&gt;                                 &lt;label for="q7